EXTRACTED VALUE: Floaty physics and an underwhelming sense of speed add up to a decent, but not great, sci-fi racing game.
It's a shame that for every step forward, Two Worlds takes about five steps back.
Could have been much better, unfortunately though this game has far too many flaws for us to recommend it to anyone.
Rocketmen: Axis of Evil offers up some interesting concepts, but the muddled execution bogs it down.
Baja aspire to be a simulation, yet it ends up losing its appeal in the process
It's the online play that sets Fuzion Frenzy 2 apart from its peers, while the rest of the package simply does its job without ever excelling.
Not for fans of videogames. [Issue 23, p.78]
